{"id":324719,"name":"Githyanki Empire","created_at":"2024-10-01T22:49:27.000000Z","updated_at":"2024-11-06T17:22:05.000000Z","is_private":0,"is_defunct":0,"organisation_id":330574,"entity":{"id":6752078,"entity_id":324719,"parent_id":null,"type_id":4,"name":"Githyanki Empire","type":"Empire","entry":"<div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">The Githyanki are a faction working for an ancient Aboleth named Xul'koroth, the \"Patron.\"<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"bullet normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"width:1.125rem;\">\u25cf<\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Azara, a Githzerai, betrayed her city by delivering a Netherese Globe to the Githyanki.<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"bullet normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"width:1.125rem;\">\u25cf<\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Vordekai gave Githyanki brains and hearts to Githzerai guards as a gruesome gift.<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"bullet normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"width:1.125rem;\">\u25cf<\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Vordekai later theorized about incorporating a time crystal into his phylactery to manipulate time and prolong his unlife. He envisioned using this artefact to rapidly age Githyanki.<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"bullet normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"width:1.125rem;\">\u25cf<\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Zorvath, a Netherese mage, mentioned that the Githyanki are pawns in Xul'koroth's cosmic game to gather Netherese Globes and ascend to godhood.<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:1.25rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">The sources suggest that the Githyanki Empire is involved in a multiversal conflict orchestrated by Xul'koroth. Their objective is to collect Netherese Globes, powerful artefacts that could potentially grant Xul'koroth divine power. They are enemies of the Githzerai, another faction mentioned in the sources.<\/span><\/div><p><\/p>","is_private":0,"tooltip":null,"is_template":null,"is_attributes_private":0,"focus_x":null,"focus_y":null,"created_at":"2024-10-01T22:49:27.000000Z","updated_at":"2024-11-06T17:22:05.000000Z","created_by":275646,"updated_by":275646,"image_path":null,"image_uuid":"9d44c2bf-198f-4135-9c0f-e3958d2af065","header_image":null,"header_uuid":null,"marketplace_uuid":null,"relationships":[{"id":686597,"owner_id":6752078,"target_id":6752071,"relation":"Vassal","visibility_id":1,"mirror_id":686598,"attitude":null,"is_pinned":0,"colour":"","marketplace_uuid":null}]},"members":[],"pivotLocations":[]}